  "prompt": "Will people without college have jobs in the future?",
  "response": "Yes, people without college degrees will continue to have job opportunities in the future. Many industries and roles do not require a four-year degree, such as:\n\n1. Skilled trades\n- Electricians\n- Plumbers\n- Mechanics\n- Construction workers\n\n2. Technology and digital roles\n- Coding bootcamp graduates\n- Web developers\n- IT support\n- Cybersecurity technicians\n\n3. Service industry\n- Restaurant management\n- Hospitality\n- Retail leadership\n- Customer service\n\n4. Healthcare support roles\n- Medical assistants\n- Dental hygienists\n- Pharmacy technicians\n\n5. Transportation and logistics\n- Truck drivers\n- Warehouse workers\n- Delivery personnel\n\n6. Sales and entrepreneurship\n- Sales representatives\n- Small business owners\n- Real estate agents\n\nWhile a college degree can provide advantages, there will always be demand for skilled workers without traditional four-year degrees. Continuous learning, skill development, and obtaining certifications can help people remain competitive in the job market.\n\nThe key is to:\n- Develop marketable skills\n- Stay adaptable\n- Pursue ongoing training\n- Be open to emerging industries",
